ast.name: Lisp for Touchdevelop
ast.comment:
"Lisp for Touchdevelop" is a short implementation of the Lisp programming language written in Touchdevelop, bundled with a code editor. Running the app will bring up the code editor, along with several examples and a help manual. For more information, run the program and click "help".

Note: This app is a work-in-progress, and may not be fully compliant lisp, or may crash if you try doing something quirky.

body.text: Wrapping multiple expressions in a single "begin" expression
